com.ibm.team.scm.common.dto

Interface IAncestorReport


  • public interface IAncestorReport
    For a particular versionable item, its ancestor report describes all of the hierarchical ancestors to them in the configuration, along with their name in the parent folder, as obtained through the use of the IConfiguration.locateAncestors(List) operation.
    Since:
    0.5

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List getNameItemPairs()
      Returns the sequence of name-item pairs leading from a root folder to a particular item.

    • Method Detail

      • getNameItemPairs

        java.util.List getNameItemPairs()
        Returns the sequence of name-item pairs leading from a root folder to a particular item. An empty sequence means the item is not present. The first element corresponds to a root folder and the last element corresponds to the versionable item itself. The first name-item pair (only) will have a null name (because root folders are by definition uncataloged in any other folder); all item handles within the ancestor report carry state ids.
        Returns:
        a possibly empty list of name-item pairs (element type: INameItemPair); never null; clients must not modify list
